How the information is used by us<br>
The information is used by us to:<br>
- Provide the best service.<br>
We provide our services/products from our local offices in different languages, and we’re here to help 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Sharing your relevant details our customer service staff allows us to respond when you need us – including responding to any questions you might have about the services/products.<br>
- Personalize the service to you<br>
The main goal here is to optimize and customize our services/products to your needs, making them easier and more enjoyable to use.<br>
- Verify that you are above the age limit to use the service.<br>
The services/products offered by ABC Mobile OÜ are not directed at children under 18 years old. For children younger than 18 years old, the use of any of our services/products is only allowed with the valid consent of a parent or a guardian. If we become aware that we process information of a child under 18 years old without the valid consent of a parent or guardian, we reserve the right to delete it.<br>
- Interact with you and update you on news, important notices (offers & promotions) via email, mail, phone or text message/SMS. When you use our services/products, we can send you the message with “login” and “password” to access the service/product or apps.<br>
In addition to that we might send you a questionnaire or invite you to submit a review about your experience with our services/products and other content. If you do not wish to be contacted about our offers, promotions or news, you can unsubscribe from our emails, text message/SMS.<br>
- Prevent fraud (Promotion of a safe and trustworthy service).<br>
In order to create a trustworthy environment for you, we might use personal data for the detection and prevention of fraud and other illegal or unwanted activities. Similarly, we might use personal data for risk assessment and security purposes, including the authentication of users. For such purposes, we might have to stop certain services or put services on hold until we've finished our assessment.<br>
We may also use and process your information and content, using different technologies to the following purposes:<br>
To enforce the Terms of Use or Privacy Policy;<br>
To contact you when we believe it to be necessary;<br>
To detect abuse and illegal activity; to detect and prevent misappropriation, infringements, identity theft and other illegal activities and misuse of the Services and/or Products;<br>
To handle breakdowns and malfunctions;<br>
To take any action in any case of dispute, or legal proceeding of any kind between you and the Services and/or Products, or between you and other users or third parties with respect to, or in relation with the Services and/or Products;<br>
For purposes provided under this Privacy Policy and Terms of Use;<br>
To help improve the safety and reliability of our Services and Products. This includes detecting, preventing, and responding to security risks, and technical issues that could harm us, our users, or the public;<br>
- Comply with regulatory requirements.<br>
Personal data submitted is sent to and stored on secure servers located in the European Economic Area according to REGULATION (EU) 2016/679 OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data.<br>
- Research, analyze, update or enhance the services we provide.<br>
We also use personal data for analytical purposes and measurement to understand how our services are used. This is part of our mission to improve our services and enhance the user experience, but can also be used for testing purposes, troubleshooting, and improving the functionality and quality of our services/products and content. We strive to only use pseudonymized data for these analytical purposes.<br>
We may also monitor and record calls you make or receive when using our services for the purposes of quality control (Call monitoring). And if you contact us, we may keep a record of your request in order to help solve any issues you might be facing.<br>
<br>
We’ll ask for your consent before using your information for a purpose that isn’t covered in this Privacy Policy.<br>
